Al-Fasher â€” The UN Secretary General Special Representative for Combating Sexual Violence in Conflict Zones, Pamela Payne has affirmed the UN keenness to end sexual violence in conflict zones , referring to the presence of strategies for preventing it , specially, in conflict zones. The UN official who met, Tuesday, in AL-Fasher, Minister of Social Welfare, in North Darfur, in the presence of the Official Responsible for Combating Sexual Violence Unit , at the Justice Ministry, said her visit to Darfur comes in the context of following up and assessment of the big progress achieved in security and stability field beside, exchanging views and information on curbing the sexual violence. The meeting also, addressed by the Minister of Social Welfare who affirmed his government commitment to cooperate with the UN in this connection.